records.title: Once Twice Melody
records.description: Eighth Studio Album from Beach House

records.title: The New Abnormal
records.description: The NYC band’s first album in seven years is mellow and slight, rendering their signature sound as the perfect background music.

records.title: WANDERKID
records.description: WANDERKID is a standout jangle pop album of 2021, thematic in its tones and structures.

records.title: CINEMA
records.description: Cinema is a gorgeous album that, as described by lead singer María Zardoya, offers listeners a break away from real life for a while to create some kind of dream world in their heads.

records.title: Private Space
records.description: Developed after being apart for much of the year, Durand Jones and the Indications' Private Space, the group's third album, is creatively explosive and delights in upending expectations

records.title: Valentine
records.description: Lindsey Jordan’s exquisite second album documents love in all stages, but mostly in disrepair. She takes on a larger and poppier sound while keeping her songwriting dazzlingly sharp and passionate.

records.title: Glow On
records.description: The Baltimore band’s spectacular fourth record is all groove, riffs, and passion. It is not a crossover hardcore album that looks to transcend the genre, but one that tries to elevate it to its highest visibility.

records.title: Call Me If You Get Lost
records.description: With DJ Drama in tow, Tyler thrives in the realm of the rap mixtape, which allows him great freedom to explore every facet of his talent as a producer, writer, and vocalist.
